<subSubSection id="B2D6B2DC4169E96D6BCDD51BFB0D2658" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FA73E1574169E96D6BCDD51BFB0D2658" blockId="65.[151,1436,882,1086]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454169E96D6BCDD51BFED321ED" bold="true" box="[151,260,883,907]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64169E96D6A4CD51AFE0321EC" author="Dahlbom, G." box="[278,468,882,906]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" refId="ref67613" refString="Dahlbom, G. (1835) Conspectus Tenthredinidum, Siricidum et Orussinorum scandinaviae quas Hymenopterorum familias. Kongl. Swenska Wetenskaps Academiens Handlingar, Havniae, 16 pp." type="book" year="1835">Dahlbom (1835)</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44169E96D6972D51BFD0B21ED" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1835" box="[552,732,883,907]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erichsoni">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454169E96D6972D51BFD0B21ED" box="[552,732,883,907]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Xyela erichsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as follows: “ 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44169E96D6827D51BFBE221ED" authority="Erichsoni" authorityName="Erichsoni" box="[893,1077,883,907]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454169E96D6827D51BFBE221ED" box="[893,1077,883,907]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Xyela Erichsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mih. nov. sp.—Jemtlandia, D. Boheman”. This taxon has been treated as available, e.g., by 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64169E96D680AD5FEFC3D21C8" author="Hartig, T." box="[848,1002,918,942]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" refId="ref68461" refString="Hartig, T. (1837) Die Aderflugler Deutschlands mit besonderer Berucksichtigung ihres Larvenzustandes und ihres Wirkens in Waldern und Garten fur Entomologen, Wald- und Gartenbesitzer. Erster Band. In: Hartig. T.: Die Familien der Blattwespen und Holzwespen nebst einer allgemeinen Einleitung zur Naturgeschichte der Hautflugler. Haude und Spener, Berlin, 416 pp." type="book" year="1837">Hartig (1837)</bibRefCitation>
but as unknown to the author, and by 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64169E96D6BCDD5D2FEF921B4" author="Klima, A." box="[151,302,954,978]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref69017" refString="Klima, A. (1937) Xyelidae. In: Hedicke, H. (ed.) Hymenopterorum Catalogus. ' s-Gravenhage, Junk, 4, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1937">Klima (1937)</bibRefCitation>
under 
<emphasis id="C8B83D454169E96D6A27D5D3FD8C21B5" box="[381,603,955,979]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">species inquirendae</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64169E96D6930D5D2FCFF21B4" author="Thomson, C. G." box="[618,808,954,978]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" refId="ref72178" refString="Thomson, C. G. (1871) Tenthredo et Sirex Lin. In: Hymenoptera Scandinaviae. H. Ohlsson, Lundae, 1, 342 pp." type="book" year="1871">Thomson (1871)</bibRefCitation>
, who had studied Dahlbom’s material, did not take note of it. 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64169E96D6B84D5B6FEAA2190" author="Hartig, T." box="[222,381,990,1014]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" refId="ref68461" refString="Hartig, T. (1837) Die Aderflugler Deutschlands mit besonderer Berucksichtigung ihres Larvenzustandes und ihres Wirkens in Waldern und Garten fur Entomologen, Wald- und Gartenbesitzer. Erster Band. In: Hartig. T.: Die Familien der Blattwespen und Holzwespen nebst einer allgemeinen Einleitung zur Naturgeschichte der Hautflugler. Haude und Spener, Berlin, 416 pp." type="book" year="1837">Hartig (1837)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64169E96D6AE5D5B6FD4B2190" author="Dalla Torre, C. G. de" box="[447,668,990,1014]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" refId="ref67681" refString="Dalla Torre, C. G. de (1894) Catalogus Hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Volumen I: Tenthredinidae incl. Uroceridae (Phyllophaga &amp; Xylophaga). G. Engelmann, Lipsiae, viii + 459 pp." type="book" year="1894">Dalla Torre (1894)</bibRefCitation>
listed it as 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44169E96D6869D5B6FC742190" authorityName=": Hartig" authorityYear="1837" box="[819,931,990,1014]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erichsonii">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454169E96D6869D5B6FC742190" box="[819,931,990,1014]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">erichsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an unjustified emendation. 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64169E96D6FA2D5B6FA4B2190" author="Schedl, W." box="[1272,1436,990,1014]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="97 - 115" refId="ref70996" refString="Schedl, W. (1978) Die Xyelidae Europas (Insecta: Hymenoptera, Symphyta, Xyelidae) mit besonderer Berucksichtigung der Fundnachweise aus den Ostalpen. Berichte des Naturwissenschaftlich-Medizinischen Vereins in Innsbruck, 65, 97 - 115." type="journal article" year="1978">Schedl (1978)</bibRefCitation>
associated 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44169E96D6A48D26BFE4D267D" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1835" box="[274,410,1027,1051]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erichsoni">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454169E96D6A48D26BFE4D267D" box="[274,410,1027,1051]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">X. erichsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44169E96D6A87D26BFD99267D" authorityName="Benson" authorityYear="1938" box="[477,590,1027,1051]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyelatana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454169E96D6A87D26BFD99267D" box="[477,590,1027,1051]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Xyelatana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44169E96D6922D26BFCC1267D" authorityName=", Dalman" authorityYear="1819" box="[632,790,1027,1051]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longula">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454169E96D6922D26BFCC1267D" box="[632,790,1027,1051]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Xyela longula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group). The name has to be set aside as a 
<emphasis id="C8B83D454169E96D6FA7D26BFA4B267D" box="[1277,1436,1027,1051]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">nomen nudum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64169E96D6BC4D24EFEF22658" author="Smith, D. R." box="[158,293,1062,1086]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 193" refId="ref71463" refString="Smith, D. R. (1978) Suborder Symphyta (Xyelidae, Pararchexyelidae, Parapamphiliidae, Xyelydidae, Karatavidae, Gigasiricidae, Sepulciidae, Pseudosiricidae, Anaxyelidae, Siricidae, Xiphydriidae, Paroryssidae, Xyelotomidae, Blasticotomidae, Pergidae). In: van der Vecht, J. &amp; Shenefelt, R. D. (eds) Hymenopterorum Catalogus (nova editio). W. Junk Publishers, The Hague, 14, 1 - 193." type="journal article" year="1978">Smith 1978</bibRefCitation>
), because it was not accompanied by an original description (Art. 12.1, 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64169E96D6F13D24EFB1A2658" author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[1097,1229,1062,1086]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" refId="ref68748" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth Edition. London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
